<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<PackageManifest Version="2.0.0" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/developer/vsx-schema/2011"
                 xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/developer/vsx-schema-design/2011">
  <Metadata>
    <Identity
      Id="AtlasAIVSIX.shifty81.ArbiterAI"
      Version="0.5.0"
      Language="en-US"
      Publisher="shifty81" />
    <DisplayName>AtlasAI — AI-Powered Development Assistant</DisplayName>
    <Description xml:space="preserve">
AtlasAI integrates a fully local, self-hosted AI engine directly into Visual Studio 2022.

FEATURES:
• Dockable Chat Panel — conversational AI assistant (Ctrl+Alt+A)
• 9 AI Commands — Ask, Explain, Fix, Refactor, Tests, Docs, Review, Insert, Open Chat
• Inline Suggestions — AI completions triggered by // AtlasAI: comments (Roslyn-powered)
• Context Injection — active file, selection and project automatically sent with every message
• Build Event Integration — after every failed build, AI fix suggestions appear in the Error List
• Persona System — choose from AtlasAI Assistant, Coder, Teacher, Organizer personalities
• Settings Page — configure backend URL, personas, TTS, and inline suggestions (Tools → Options → AtlasAI)

PRIVACY:
All AI inference runs on your own hardware via the self-hosted AtlasAI backend (Python / FastAPI).
No code, prompts, or telemetry is ever sent to any third-party cloud service.

REQUIREMENTS:
• Visual Studio 2022 (17.x) — Community, Professional, or Enterprise
• Arbiter backend running locally (see https://github.com/shifty81/MasterRepoRefactor for setup)
    </Description>
    <Tags>AI, code assistant, chat, refactor, autocomplete, local LLM, copilot, offline</Tags>
    <ProjectUrl>https://github.com/shifty81/MasterRepoRefactor</ProjectUrl>
    <License>MIT</License>
    <Icon>Resources\arbiter_icon.png</Icon>
    <GettingStartedGuide>https://github.com/shifty81/MasterRepoRefactor#readme</GettingStartedGuide>
    <ReleaseNotes>
v0.5.0 — Initial VSIX release
  • Chat panel (WebView2, full AtlasAI IDE interface)
  • 9 context-aware AI commands with keyboard shortcuts
  • Inline code suggestions via Roslyn InlineCompletionsProvider
  • Build-event hook: AI fix suggestions surfaced in the Error List (M6-10)
  • Settings page (Tools → Options → AtlasAI)
  • Auto-detects AtlasAI backend on ports 8001 (Engine) and 8000 (Bridge)
    </ReleaseNotes>
    <MoreInfo>https://github.com/shifty81/MasterRepoRefactor/blob/main/VisualStudioExtension/INSTALL.md</MoreInfo>
  </Metadata>
  <Installation>
    <InstallationTarget Id="Microsoft.VisualStudio.Community"    Version="[17.0,18.0)" />
    <InstallationTarget Id="Microsoft.VisualStudio.Professional" Version="[17.0,18.0)" />
    <InstallationTarget Id="Microsoft.VisualStudio.Enterprise"   Version="[17.0,18.0)" />
  </Installation>
  <Dependencies>
    <Dependency Id="Microsoft.Framework.NDP"
                DisplayName=".NET Framework"
                Version="[4.7.2,)" />
    <Dependency Id="Microsoft.VisualStudio.Component.CoreEditor"
                DisplayName="Visual Studio core editor"
                Version="[17.0,18.0)" />
  </Dependencies>
  <Prerequisites>
    <Prerequisite Id="Microsoft.VisualStudio.Component.CoreEditor"
                  Version="[17.0,18.0)"
                  DisplayName="Visual Studio core editor" />
  </Prerequisites>
  <Assets>
    <Asset Type="Microsoft.VisualStudio.VsPackage"
           d:Source="Project"
           d:ProjectName="%CurrentProject%"
           Path="|AtlasAIVSIX;PkgdefProjectOutputGroup|" />
    <Asset Type="Microsoft.VisualStudio.MefComponent"
           d:Source="Project"
           d:ProjectName="%CurrentProject%"
           Path="|AtlasAIVSIX|" />
  </Assets>
</PackageManifest>
